  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed across key boundary condition inputs including inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity; a screening sensitivity study was conducted internally to rank input contributions to hemolysis index variance. Probabilistic bounds on the relative hemolysis index are reported at the 95th percentile. The UQ analysis confirms that prediction uncertainty does not alter the accept/reject outcome under the RH < 1 criterion.",
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-cpb-hemolysis",
