      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in vitro measurements at 5 flow-speed combinations. Mean relative error 8.3%; all predictions within experimental uncertainty bands. RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all assessed conditions."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-mesh-convergence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence and discretization error assessment",
      "description": "Richardson extrapolation applied to three mesh levels (4.2M, 9.8M, 18.6M cells). Grid convergence index (GCI) for NIH < 2.1% on finest mesh. Discretization error classified as negligible relative to experimental scatter."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-uq-probabilistic-bounds",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Probabilistic uncertainty quantification of boundary condition inputs",
      "description": "Monte Carlo sampling (N=500) over inlet flow rate (±5%), rotational speed (±2%), and blood viscosity (±8% representing donor variability) propagated through the CFD surrogate. 95th-percentile RH reported as 0.87, confirming margin against the RH < 1 criterion. A screening sensitivity study was conducted to rank input contributions; results documented in internal technical report TR-UQ-2024-07. Dominant drivers identified verbally as viscosity and rotational speed, though structured factor rankings are not formally linked to this credibility package."
    }
  ],
