    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are consistent with MRL 2 scoping and do not represent gaps at the required gradation. Uncertainty quantification confirms the 95th-percentile RH of 0.87 provides adequate margin against the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The UQ analysis, including a screening sensitivity study documented in internal report TR-UQ-2024-07, supports confidence that input variability does not alter the regulatory conclusion. The credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD model is sufficiently credible for its intended use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
